    "instructions": [
      "Step 1 — Unpack & sort (2 min): Fridge items: milk, all yoghurt tubs, all hummus tubs, spinach bags, bananas, apples, rotisserie chickens. Pantry items: Weet-Bix, protein powder, rice pouches, pasta pouches, pasta sauce, crackers, bars, peanut butter, sauce, psyllium husk (if purchased).",
      "Step 2 — Pull & portion chicken (5 min): Open the first rotisserie chicken. Using your hands and a fork, pull all breast and thigh meat off the bones into chunks. Discard skin. Divide into 4 containers, ~200g per container. Seal, label Day 1 (Fri), Day 2 (Sat), Day 3 (Sun), Day 4 (Mon). Refrigerate immediately. Do NOT open the second chicken yet.",
      "Step 3 — Portion snack bags (2 min): Count out 7 Carman's bars. Place 1 bar per zip-lock bag (7 bags total). Label Mon-Sun. Apples stay whole on the bench or in the fridge.",
      "Step 4 — Set up breakfast station (1 min): Place Weet-Bix box, protein powder, and peanut butter jar together on the bench. Milk stays in fridge. No pre-mixing — assemble fresh each morning.",
      "Step 5 — Set up lunch station (2 min): Stack 14 tuna tins (olive oil) together in the pantry — grab 2 each day at lunch. Place crackers, hummus tubs, and spinach bags visible in fridge.",
      "Step 6 — Organize fridge (2 min): Top shelf: chicken containers (Day 1-4), yoghurt tubs, milk. Middle shelf: hummus tubs, spinach bags. Door: sauces, parmesan.",
      "Step 7 — Set up pantry station (1 min): Group rice pouches, pasta pouches, pasta sauce jar, tuna tins (springwater, for Tue-Thu dinners), and parmesan in one section.",
      "Mid-week restock (Tue 17 Mar, ~8 min): Open second rotisserie chicken — pull all meat, store in 1 container for buffer/contingency. Open 3rd spinach bag. Open 3rd yoghurt tub if needed. Tidy and re-organize fridge."
